The <span style="color: #6D5298;">Christian Socialists</span> within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> have been wanting to separate themselves for a while now, the Young Plan referendum debacle has given them the pretext. During the vote on the "Freedom Law" in the Reichstag, they went against Westarp's compromise solution and denounced Hugenberg, causing him to expel the renegade deputies. They were soon joined in leaving the party by many members of the "Young Conservative" faction. 

However, the failure of them to bring the party organizations or the <span style="color: #385A38;">agrarian</span> wing with them has mitigated the impact. Westarp has stayed within the party, leading the remaining moderates. Despite their hopes of ousting Hugenberg in the future, his position within the party has been bolstered by the departure. [? if stegerwald_path: The <span style="color: #6D5298;">Christian Socialists</span> have found refuge within the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>, and will shift the party rightwards with their nationalistic views. ?]

