[? if young_plan_signatures < 10: The failure of the Young Plan referendum to reach the 10% threshold?][? if tariffs < -1 or land_reform > 0: The all-or-nothing policy of Hugenberg leaving the party unable to enter government and revert our [? if land_reform >= 1: land reform policies?][? if land_reform >= 1 and tariffs < -1: and ?][? if tariffs < -1: tariff reductions?]?], and the declining popularity of the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has convinced the majority of the party to vote out Hugenberg. He is replaced with Treviranus, a member of the "Young Conservative" wing of the party. The Young Conservatives are in favor of governmental participation, advancing their goals in the framework of the system. However, the national conservatives retain heavy control over the party and the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> isn't exactly a democratic party yet. [? if stegerwald_path: This leaves the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> as a more nationalistic, conservative alternative to the <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>. ?]

In response, Hugenberg threatens to take himself and his supporters into a new splinter party, which could cripple the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>, especially since he has worked to eliminate moderate influences within the party organizations, who are likely to follow him.

